        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:50AM CDT by NWS Norman OK</headline>
        <description>At 450 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 3 miles north of Concho to 4 miles west of
Lookeba. Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Oklahoma City, El Reno, Yukon, Piedmont, Hinton, Union
City, Geary, Okarche, Binger, Calumet, Eakly, Lookeba, Bridgeport,
Cogar, Concho, Cedar Lake, and Richland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
